+
+component_id: README
+component_layer: SUB_SKILL
+component_name: Readme
+route_families: UNKNOWN_NEEDS_REVIEW
+activation_triggers: route_family in [UNKNOWN_NEEDS_REVIEW] or explicit registry selection; mark UNKNOWN_NEEDS_REVIEW only when route_family is unknown.
+upstream_inputs: director_intent_packet, stage_execution_packet, research_brief_packet, script_segment_packet as applicable.
+downstream_outputs: stage_execution_packet, skill_activation_packet, atomic_task_packet, media_context_packet, quality_report_packet as applicable.
+required_input_packets: See runtime_contracts/UNIVERSAL_COMPONENT_CONTRACT_STANDARD.md and registries/communication_pointer_registry.yaml.
+emitted_output_packets: Must emit typed packet named in communication pointer registry; UNKNOWN_NEEDS_REVIEW until route-bound.
+communication_pointers: Must use registries/communication_pointer_registry.yaml; no downstream stage may run without required packet.
+quality_gates: Must provide component_quality_score, confidence, failure_modes, and pass/fail rationale.
+validator_bindings: validators/validate_mac06_1a_output.py plus future packet graph validators.
+fallback_behavior: If required input packet or validation evidence is missing, return BLOCKED_BEFORE_OUTPUT or NEEDS_HUMAN_REVIEW; do not fabricate.
+lineage_fields: upstream_packet_id, downstream_packet_id, evidence_path, source_component_id, decision_reason, timestamp_or_version.
+provider_boundary: No n8n, provider, Gemini, OpenWebUI, or media execution without explicit approval; handoff packets only by default.
+status_limits: May not claim production-ready, onboarded, provider-called, media-created, or n8n-executed without external proof.
+human_approval_points: Required for repo write, provider execution, n8n execution, media creation, full dossier, or segment regeneration approval.
+failure_modes: missing_input_packet, missing_output_schema, missing_validator_binding, missing_pointer, low_quality_score, provider_boundary_violation.
+handoff_targets: Next layer defined by communication pointer registry and selected route manifest.
